\begin_layout Section
Requirements
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Non functional requirements
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The non functional requirements for the platform have been identified as follows: 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
NF1 Reliability: the system must satisfy the functional requirements with 100% of server uptime on the back-end side, and a stable release of the user-side applications.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
The latter is achieved through constant maintenance of the applications' code bases (outside of project scope), while the former needs to be designed since the beginning of the project as it relies on specific hardware infrastructures; these include:
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Server farms replication through cloning
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Local data duplication with RAID controllers 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Data synchronization between the server farms 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Periodic memory backup on flash storage to allow for faster recovery in the event of unexpected system failures 
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
These measure should minimize the RTO and RPO parameters making them tend to zero.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
